heading: Law of total probability
text:
\(B_1, \ldots, B_k\) partition sample space, event \(\)
\[
P() = \sum_{=1}^k P(\cap B_i) = \sum_{=1}^k P(\mid B_i)P(B_i)

heading: Conditional probability mass/density
text:
Discrete case (mass):
\[
P(Y=y \mid X=x) =
\frac{P(X=x, Y=y)}{P(X=x)}
\]Discrete case (mass):\[
P(Y=y \mid X=x) =
\frac{P(X=x, Y=y)}{P(X=x)}
\]Continuous case (density):
\[
f_{Y\mid X}(y \mid x) =
\frac{f(x,y)}{f_X(x)}
\]
Conditional probability (\(R \\mathbb R\)):
\[
P(Y \R \mid X = x) = \int_R f_{Y \mid X}(y \mid x) \;dy
\]Continuous case (density):\[
f_{Y\mid X}(y \mid x) =
\frac{f(x,y)}{f_X(x)}
\]Conditional probability (\(R \\mathbb R\)):
\[
P(Y \R \mid X = x) = \int_R f_{Y \mid X}(y \mid x) \;dy
\]

heading: Example 1.16 (Picking real numbers)
text:
\(X\) uniformly distributed \((0, 1)\).\(X\) uniformly distributed \((0, 1)\).\(Y\) uniformly distributed \((0, x)\).\(Y\) uniformly distributed \((0, x)\).Find conditional distribution \(Y\) given \(X = x\).Find conditional distribution \(Y\) given \(X = x\).Find joint distribution \(X\) \(Y\).Find joint distribution \(X\) \(Y\).Find marginal density \(Y\).Find marginal density \(Y\).know \(f_X(x) = 1, \; \text{}0 < x < 1\).know \(f_X(x) = 1, \; \text{}0 < x < 1\).\(X\) gets value \(x\), \(f_{Y \mid X}(y \mid x) = 1/x, \; \text{}0 < y < x < 1\).\(X\) gets value \(x\), \(f_{Y \mid X}(y \mid x) = 1/x, \; \text{}0 < y < x < 1\).get joint distribution:
\[
\begin{aligned}
  f_{Y \mid X}(y \mid x) = \frac{f(x,y)}{f_X(x)}
  &\implies
  f(x,y) = f_{Y \mid X}(y \mid x) \cdot f_X(x) \\
  &\implies
  f(x,y) = \frac1x \cdot 1 \\
  &\implies
  f(x,y) = \frac1x
\end{aligned}
\]
\(0 < y < x < 1\).get joint distribution:\[
\begin{aligned}
  f_{Y \mid X}(y \mid x) = \frac{f(x,y)}{f_X(x)}
  &\implies
  f(x,y) = f_{Y \mid X}(y \mid x) \cdot f_X(x) \\
  &\implies
  f(x,y) = \frac1x \cdot 1 \\
  &\implies
  f(x,y) = \frac1x
\end{aligned}
\]\(0 < y < x < 1\)., marginal distribution \(Y\):
\[
\begin{aligned}
  f_Y(y)
  &= \int_{-\infty}^\infty f(x,y) \;dx \\
  &= \int_y^1 f(x,y) \;dx \\
  &= \int_y^1 \frac1x \;dx \\
  &= -\ln y
\end{aligned}
\]
\(0 < y < 1\)., marginal distribution \(Y\):\[
\begin{aligned}
  f_Y(y)
  &= \int_{-\infty}^\infty f(x,y) \;dx \\
  &= \int_y^1 f(x,y) \;dx \\
  &= \int_y^1 \frac1x \;dx \\
  &= -\ln y
\end{aligned}
\]\(0 < y < 1\).

heading: Conditional expectation of \(Y\) given \(X=x\)
text:
Discrete case:
\[
E(Y \mid X = x) = \sum_y y\; P(Y=y \mid X=x)
\]Discrete case:\[
E(Y \mid X = x) = \sum_y y\; P(Y=y \mid X=x)
\]Continuous case:
\[
E(Y \mid X = x) =
\int_{-\infty}^\infty y \; f_{Y \mid X}(y \mid x) \; dy
\]Continuous case:\[
E(Y \mid X = x) =
\int_{-\infty}^\infty y \; f_{Y \mid X}(y \mid x) \; dy
\]Note function \(x\).

heading: Example 1.18 (Independent Poisson RVs)

text:
Assume \(X\) \(Y\) joint density
\[
f(x, y) =  rac{2}{xy}, 	ext{ } 1 < y < x < e
\]Assume \(X\) \(Y\) joint density\[
f(x, y) =  rac{2}{xy}, 	ext{ } 1 < y < x < e

\[
 egin{align}
f_X(x)
&= \int_1^x f(x, y) \; dy \
&= \int_1^x  rac{2}{xy} \; dy \
&=  rac{2}{x} \int_1^x  rac{dy}{y} \
&=  rac{2\ln x}{x} & 	ext{ } 1 < x < e
\end{align}
\]
, need \(f_X(x)\):\[
 egin{align}
f_X(x)
&= \int_1^x f(x, y) \; dy \
&= \int_1^x  rac{2}{xy} \; dy \
&=  rac{2}{x} \int_1^x  rac{dy}{y} \
&=  rac{2\ln x}{x} & 	ext{ } 1 < x < e
\end{align}
\], conditional density 
\[
 egin{align}
f_{Y\mid X}(y \mid x)
&=  rac{f(x, y)}{f_X (x)} \
&=  rac{2 / xy}{2 \ln x / x} \
&=  rac{1}{y \ln x}
\end{align}
\]
, conditional density \[
 egin{align}
f_{Y\mid X}(y \mid x)
&=  rac{f(x, y)}{f_X (x)} \
&=  rac{2 / xy}{2 \ln x / x} \
&=  rac{1}{y \ln x}
\end{align}
\]conditional expectation 
\[
 egin{align}
E(Y \mid X = x)
&= \int_1^x y\; f_{Y\mid X} (y \mid x)\;dy \
&= \int_1^x y\;  rac{1}{y\;\ln x} \;dy \
&= \int_1^x  rac{dy}{\ln x} \;dy \
&=  rac1{\ln x}\int_1^x dy \
&=  rac{x - 1}{\ln x}
\end{align}

heading: Properties of conditional expectation
text:
Linearity:
\[
E(aY + bZ \mid X = x) \,=\,
\;E(Y \mid X = x) + b\;E(Z \mid X = x)
\]Linearity:\[
E(aY + bZ \mid X = x) \,=\,
\;E(Y \mid X = x) + b\;E(Z \mid X = x)
\]LOTUS:
\[
E(g(Y) \mid X = x) =
\begin{cases}
  \sum_y \;g(y)\; P(Y = y \mid X = x)
  & \text{(discrete)} \\
  \\
  \int_{-\infty}^\infty g(y)\; f_{Y\mid X}(y\mid x)\;dy
  & \text{(continuous)}
\end{cases}
\]LOTUS:\[
E(g(Y) \mid X = x) =
\begin{cases}
  \sum_y \;g(y)\; P(Y = y \mid X = x)
  & \text{(discrete)} \\
  \\
  \int_{-\infty}^\infty g(y)\; f_{Y\mid X}(y\mid x)\;dy
  & \text{(continuous)}
\end{cases}
\]Independence: \(X \bot Y\):
\[
E(Y \mid X = x) = E(Y)
\]Independence: \(X \bot Y\):\[
E(Y \mid X = x) = E(Y)
\]\(Y = g(x)\):
\[
E(Y \mid X = x) = g(x)
\]\(Y = g(x)\):\[
E(Y \mid X = x) = g(x)
\]

heading: Conditional expectation given an event
Total expectation
text:
Let \(Y\) RV.Let \(Y\) RV.Let \(A_1, \ldots, A_k\) partition sample space.Let \(A_1, \ldots, A_k\) partition sample space.
\[
E(Y) = \sum_{=1}^k E(Y \mid A_i)\;P(A_i)
\]\[
E(Y) = \sum_{=1}^k E(Y \mid A_i)\;P(A_i)
\]
